{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 — T8 (LLM/prompt structural-completeness) review.\n\nAffirmations (criteria passed):\n- No undefined-but-referenced enum/schema vocabulary: every referenced symbol exists and is specified in-tree — `_resolve_system` (passes.py:173), `AnthropicModelSettings.anthropic_cache_instructions`/`anthropic_cache_tool_definitions` (runner.py:430-435), the anthropic gate `resolved.startswith(\"anthropic\")` (runner.py:428), and `result.usage()`/RunUsage capture (runner.py:394-418). The structured output contract `plan_review_findings` is registered (passes.py:145) and unchanged by this plan.\n- Fallback for a failed/incomplete sub-step IS specified: the load-bearing spike has an explicit documented fallback chain — system-prompt caching → route stable plan through `instructions=` → user-message `CachePoint` (deferred). AC1 ties the implementation to the recorded spike outcome.\n- No ambiguous counter/state increment introduced; no new processing-protocol/schema co-location surface; no instruction-locality / pink-elephant risk (the plan explicitly makes NO user-message content-list change and NO prompt-text edit, so the structured-output retry path is untouched).\n\nOne grounded coaching item:\n\n- [ ] AC3 names the field `usage.cache_read_input_tokens` but pydantic-ai 1.107.0 NORMALIZES Anthropic's raw `cache_read_input_tokens`/`cache_creation_input_tokens` to `cache_read_tokens`/`cache_write_tokens` (see `_extract_usage` docstring + capture, runner.py:397-418 citing usage.py:194-200). Reword AC3 to assert the normalized field (`usage.cache_read_tokens > 0`, surfaced as `cache_read_tokens`) so the executor's verification key matches what the code/library actually exposes.\n  - criteria: T8\n  - location: Acceptance Criteria, AC3 (\"usage.cache_read_input_tokens > 0\")\n  - evidence: AC3 quoted phrase \"usage.cache_read_input_tokens > 0\"; runner.py:413-417 returns `cache_read_tokens`/`cache_write_tokens`; runner.py:397-400 docstring \"library NORMALIZES Anthropic's raw cache_read_input_tokens ... to cache_read_tokens / cache_write_tokens (usage.py:194-200)\". This is the one referenced field-vocabulary mismatch an executor verifying AC3 would trip on. (The SPIKE AC1 already owns pinning RunUsage field names, which mitigates this — hence light, not blocking.)\n  - suggested_fix: \"On a repeat anthropic container call (same parent plan), `usage.cache_read_tokens > 0` (pydantic-ai normalizes Anthropic's raw cache_read_input_tokens to cache_read_tokens).\""},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577519653682001,"uuid":"417563ba-46bf-4a31-beff-d57ad991fd85"}